<br>
If you are more interested in nitpicking details than the matter at hand then try this.<br>
<br>
1: I am able to &quot;write&quot; you name, what I didnt do was &quot;spell&quot; it correctly. How's that for stupid semantics? Do you find it irrelevant and irritateingly petty suggesting a weak argument? I do. <br>
<br>
2: Rather than attempt a serious reply to what was said you take the lazy option of making a groundless accusation that I dont know what fairness is, puulease! We are debating an issue here, not you, me or your english teachers level of skill. <br>
<br>
 Claiming the moral high ground as a justification for your ideas didnt work for the flat earth society and it isnt working for you. To add weight to your vaporous point you then ...repeat it. Repeating your point does not make it any more accurate than it wasn't to begin with. What it does do is make you sound like a stuck record unable to think beyond your own initial ideas.<br>
<br>
Maybe you like repetition?<br>
Maybe you like repetition?<br>
Maybe you like repetition?<br>
<br>
In which case you may recognise this, repeated from an earlier post for your repeat reading pleasure. It was after all posted as a rebuttal of your own ideas. <br>
<br>
&quot;The real problem that needs to be addressed is this situation where guilds count as one player for bookings and yet various indies can theoretically act as a pseudo guild inviteing each other but avoiding the above booking restriction. THAT IS WHAT NEEDS SOLVING. This inequity will not be fixed by swinging hard the other way with an even greater inequity.&quot;<br>
<br>
There are two points here, the first acknowledges the same problem you yourself do. <br>
<br>
The second point is where we differ. Last I checked two wrongs still dont make a right. Your solution is to simply penalise the indies, screw em, too bad for them eh.<br>
let me ask the proponents of this brilliant solution this, how long did it take you to come up with the idea? 1 second? less? <br>
<br>
I dont have an answer to this problem .....yet. Given thought and a bit of time and focussed debate however I suspect WE the community here may be able to. Making do with the first idea that pops into your head (IE ban the indies) is pitifull, it is an injustice and an insult.<br>
<br>
<br>
Either make an effort and have a go at a &quot;fair&quot; solution or shut up. This of course would mean you run the risk of having your idea critised,modified or even ridiculed, it may even no longer appear to be your idea (o the poor bruised ego's, I can hear sad violins playing) <br>
<br>
but there is one thing that definately isnt needed and thats the &quot;I told you so&quot; flat earther standing on the sidlines waving a &quot;FCFS flat earth&quot; placard and chanting there dogma over and over, confident in the knowledge that they are right, because after all, they said so. It does nothing to move us toward a solution. It isnt usefull. <br>
<br>
Im eager to participate in a debate working toward a solution, I will not be drawn into any other.<br>
<br>
Abraxax<br>
Reason is a tool; try to remember where you left it.<br>
<br>
